article.headline: Nebraska 75, Lipscomb 52
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Jason Douisseau scored a career-high 21 points to lead Nebraska to a 75-52 victory over Lipscomb on Monday night. Nebraska (8-1) took advantage of five turnovers by Lipscomb early to go up 9-0 and was up by 22 points at halftime. The Bisons (2-6) had 13 turnovers and allowed seven offensive rebounds to Nebraska in the first half. Nebraska came out flat in the second half, going more than five minutes without a basket. Lipscomb made 13 of its first 18 shots in the half and cut the lead to 12 but got no closer. Andrew Drevo added 14 points for Nebraska, while Jake Muhleisen had 12 and Nate Johnson 10. Brian Fisk led Lipscomb with 20 points, while James Poindexter had 12.
